Decided to stop by there for lunch. Asked to use the bathroom, being 8 month pregnant, but they declined saying they have very strict rules and can’t let me go. I totally understand it due to the whole COVID situation, but I think for a women who is 8 month pregnant there could be an exception. Went somewhere else for lunch.

Great tacos and quick, friendly service. Good option for a quick but tasty lunch in the area
Sadly to say the chicken(the main part of the taco el pastor) was overload, dry and hard to chew! Gotta keep that tender and chewable please!
Me and boyfriend loooove this place eat here often
Great tacos! And they let you put as much salsa as you want (as they should !)
Decent Taco terrible management. Not willing to even serve fresh cut meat. Very disappointed by managers who do a terrible job.

The portion generous and the people nice, but the al pastor taco was just dripping in oil, and lacking flavor. Tacos are advertised as $3.75 each, but I was charged $8.50 for the two (it should have been $8.17)

Ordered burrito bowl with the grilled cactus and chips and salsa. This was probably the worst Mexican food I’ve had in the city, do not recommend. Cactus was undercooked, dish lacked flavor and the sauces tasted watered down. Salsa was flavorless and chips were poor. I don’t leave reviews but I advise against eating here.
Came here from Los Angeles and I can honestly say this is the best chicken taco I’ve ever had. Better than anything in LA.
Taste is really good I like it and ordered again. 👍
The food is delicious
Tasty tacos

Grabbed a tasty, quick lunch here. Got a Nopal burrito bowl (had great flavor) and a side of chips and salsa. Will definitely be back, just took away a star because the meal was a more expensive than what I was expecting. Tacos might be more budget friendly.

Best tacos in this area hands down. The tacos might be a bit overpriced, but it’s expected for DUMBO. I recommend getting one or each and trying the hot salsa as well.  I have been here a few times and I have had a positive experience each time.
I like the burrito bowl. I’ve only had the pork which is nice. My friend tried all three in the form of tacos and said that each was delicious.
Delicious flavor. Mad expensive for the portions, but it's DUMBO...
Owner has an attitude he can’t back up. One block over better tacos

The first time I went there was a couple of weeks ago, and the tacos were good.  Decided to go back today and they were much better than before.  Maybe it's the time of day or where they cut the meat from this time around, but the pork was tender, juicy and flavorful.  The chicken tack is good, but not as good as the al pastor.  Also, I did put their hot sauce on my tacos this time, so maybe that made the difference?  Dunno, but it was good.  My only "complaint" is that they play their music way too loud inside the restaurant.  Makes it hard to order and to understand others.

Paid $14 for a small tray of food half way filled. Walked a few blocks to find a spot to stop and eat only to open the tray and it look like somebody threw up in a tray and gave it to me.  Not to mention the corn in the cup was missing ingredients.  If I could post pics here I would show you exactly how bad it was.  Too bad too because it was better service at one point.
We got two tacos and a taco bowl and a Mexican Coke. All amazing. Great service. Great food!  Would recommend for a quick and affordable bite.

My eyes lit up seeing the restaurant's name knowing how tasteful Tacos Al Pastor can be but unfortunately I do not recommend this place to anyone.  Low quality food from what seems to be a 'Local Business'  GENUINE RECOMMENDATION: Tacos Mix 234 E 116th St  Ny, NY (UPPER EAST SIDE)
Very good taste
Worst experience ever. Owner/boss  very unprofessional toward customers and employees.

Taste good. Ordered Burrito Bowl, usually that means with the tortilla bread, no bread here unfortunately. Very misleading should just say Bowl! But flavor and serving were good (for Dumbo) had pork and chicken burrito bowls. I asked if pork was spicy was told no, ended up having giant pieces of jalapenos in it, which I dislike, so I was left unsatisfied picking at my friend's chicken bowl. Doubt I'd personally go here again, but wasnt horrible.
Best Tacos in Brooklyn, and it's not even close. They make the corn tortillas by hand right in front of you, and the meat is delicious. Always worth swinging by when in Dumbo!

Nice people but bad value for the price. $3.75 for the smallest taco I’ve ever had in my life (I’m from SoCal so ive had my share of tacos). Ordered 2, with tax paid about $8 and was still hungry after...would not return or recommend. I would suggest they fill those tacos way more so people aren’t disappointed...the meat wasn’t even good quality either...worse than fast food. Sorry i hate to be mean but that was my experience.

Best tacos Al Pastor in the city! Corn hand made tortilla! Meat is super juicy and plenty of it! I go there twice a weekend it never disappoints. I do like chicken better then pork but either one is great! It's not sit down to eat - it is to take it to go place.
Coming from LA I missed a good pastor taco. I saw the trompo from outside and had to try them. The flour tortillas don’t hold up to Sonora but the corn is solid. The tacos are great enough said.

Beware this restaurant is not affiliated with Los Tacos No.1 in Manhattan. Went here last night because all the signs are so similar to Los Tacos No.1. It wasn't as good so later on we ended up going to the real Los Tacos No.1 in Chelsea Market. The staff at the real Los Tacos told us that this restaurant is not affiliated with them.

Good but overpriced .  Cooks were good .. cashier.. ehh... quantity for value ... ehhh
My friend tried tacos for the first time in his life and liked them. We got cactus tacos and chicken tacos.
If you are in to really dry meat in your tacos this is the place to go. We got the pork and chicken pastor tacos.
Delicous
Guy at the register seriously rude and the food in this place is bad...

Pretty disappointing. I work nearby and was excited to hear that there was a Los Tacos in Brooklyn as I’m used to going to one of the Manhattan locations. I ordered a chicken bowl. Not only was the bowl on the smaller side, the rice was underdone and crunchy, and the chicken was hard. Pretty frustrating considering it’s a $14 bowl
Al pastor bowl is delicious. They also have tasty salsas.
2 types of meat tacos, 1 vegetarian taco, great salsas and toppings and option for chips & guac and Jarritos Mexican soda. Good service. Only problem is all their plates and utensils are disposable 😢
Amazing tacos and taco bowl! Limited places to sit, so take out is probably a better option! But the food is amazing
Great tacos and bowls.
Tasty but very overpriced
Good but not anything to write home about.
Best tacos in Brooklyn take your pick pork al pastor or chicken.

Limited menu and overpriced. Bland interior as well. Feels like someone trying to make a quick buck on a tourist neighborhood with as little effort as possible.
Wonderful addition to the neighborhood! Great food, great staff. I hope they don't get pushed out because of the crazy Dumbo rent increases.

Terrible food, definitely will never order from this place again. After waiting an hour for my food, the food arrived and looked like throw up. I couldnt separate the tacos since it was all so mixed up. Over peppered and definitely not worth it. Look at the advertising they give on seamless and how the food actually looks. Discusting

Not nearly as good as the times square location. By quality of food I wouldn't even think it's the same company.. the only thing linking the two places is their typography and branding. The menu here is sub par at the best.
Some of the best al pastor tacos I have ever had!!!

I didn't like the rice, but the meat was cooked well. The place was very hot and had very limited seating. Tacos were a bit over prices in my option. I did not like the style of tortilla, but it was flavorful.

Honestly these are my favorite tacos & burrito bowls in Dumbo. Being able to watch them make everything fresh is great and the food is too delicious for words. Treat yourself. I usually get the chicken burrito bowl with everything. After you order, remember to hand them your receipt, don't just stand there expecting someone to read your mind. Be friendly. Everyone there is nice.
Highly Overrated - these tacos weren't worth the cost. They didn't taste bad but far from deserving the enormous hype from local media.
Great price for the area
Best Al Pastor in NYC, authentic Mexico City style but with massive portions.
Amazing tacos!!!
Rude service refused to give money back when asked for it.
Great cactus, chicken, pork and staff! Won’t go wrong with bowls or tacos!
Cheap, tasty tacos
Loved the food. Seating is a bit limited but it's not an issue, especially when the weather is nice.
Not the same owner as Los Tacos in Manhattan yet it looks identical...

These tacos are actually quite strong, it's tough to consider this an 'everyday' lunch spot though with the prices being pretty elevated for tacos. Still a good spot for a quick bite if you're in the mood.
Decent tacos. Good for a quick lunch time bite in DUMBO.
Amazing tacos and esquitte! Will definitely be coming back many times.
I’m a picky Texan when it comes to tacos, but I love this place! The tacos al pastor are made with a kebab style rotisserie and it’s delicious. Nice fast, casual choice in Dumbo, but limited seating.
Mighty good eats at this funky local spot. Had an Al Pastor salad. Would go back. - cora
CHICKEN TACOS OMGGGGG... SOO GOODD
I was very surprised on how good the tacos were! I am very pleased with the food and the friendly service. Highly recommend this place!
Tacos are good. This is close to the ones you would find in Mexico City. I like the chicken better though. Salsas are delicious too.
Good tacos al pastor. They didn’t give me a glass of water and the sauces are not spice enough.
Amazing Pork Tacos! love the pineapple touch.. love the taco shells, awesome place. prices are awesome.
DELICIOUS tacos!  I cannot rate this higher than 5stars or I would. My girlfriend is from the Southwest and she says these are the closest to real tacos she has had here in NY.
Los Tacos No. 1 should sue for attempted impersonation. Same menu, containers for salsa, ticket process, tile floor, even typography. Except the food can't hold a candle. It's mediocre at best
Just moved back to BK from Austin Texas and I have been searching for decent tacos. These are beyond decent, they would be upper level even in Austin. Five Yums.
Best tacos al pastor in Brooklyn maybe even NYC
Small space with barely any seating. The options are limited but everything on the menu is great. Recommend the chicken or pork burrito bowl.
Fresh tasting tacos roasted corn with cheese healthy salads and burritos and bowls are delicious reasonably priced clean place
Great taco's, try their Mexican street corn as well!

Good, in fact very good! It appears to be the same people as los tacos no. 1 and if so I am going to pray every day to the taco gods that they add carne asada and mulas to the menu, if they did I would achieve an unparalleled state of taco-induced nirvana (and my rating would be a 5)
Mighty fine tacos, simple menu counter service, good food! Will be back
Food is mediocre. Avoid this place. Many better options in the neighborhood
Had the burrito bowl and it was excellent!  Not many places in DUMBO that offer a quick meal.  Fast service and everything tasted very fresh.  will be coming back here for lunch.

No seating and $3.75 tacos. They keep it simple, so just depends on your taste. Los Tacos is fine for the price and speed and there’s seating outside in dumbo. The staff and food is nice but $13-ish for a salad bowl is a bit pricey if I’m being honest. Can’t knock Los Tacos too much, good lil food place. Bienvenidos! 3/5 Stars

Great tacos, great taco bowl.  Solid salsa.  Not so good chips.  Very strange system where you have to take your receipt and hand it to the chef (why don't they do this for you?).  They do take credit cards now.

Our corporate office moved from Chelsea to DUMBO, and one of the biggest losses was Los Tacos No. 1 in Chelsea Market. 😭  Word spread quickly that there was a new taco joint near the new office bearing the same name, so a few of us ventured in for lunch today, and arrived to a line trailing out of the door.  Unfortunately, long lines don't always correlate with quality. Los Tacos Al Pastor is a very small, unassuming place with no seating. It looks like it tries to emulate its Chelsea cousin in style and menu, but that is where the similarities end. It lacks in flavor, and you can see this plainly in observing the meat on the spits, which lacks the char and seasonings which give Los Tacos No. 1's meats their color. The flavor profile at Al Pastor is much milder, and there aren't as many options on the menu. (Where's the beef?!)  That said, Los Tacos Al Pastor remains a solid option around DUMBO, and a step above Taco Dumbo. I was really happy to see they had piña (pineapple) flavored Jarritos, and that the lines moved very quickly, given the lack of tourists.  Enjoy but know there is no comparison to el primero en Chelsea.

I grew up in Texas and never like any Mexican places up north, but this place is amazing. It's very authentic with a small menu (pork or chicken pastor and nopales in tacos, salads, or bowls) and damn their pastor and tortillas are delicious. Good salsas too.

Had / still have high hopes for this taco joint, but their tacos / burrito bowls are just lower quality for the higher dumbo bk price point.  I'd put the quality in the "quick tourist taco from a cart" grade  for like $1-2 dollar per taco, but $4 and change per taco for the quality isn't even close. they seem to use a lot of lower-end mass produced ingredients and chaotic open kitchen-style with busy staff creates risk for error. won't be back. way better quality of tacos for the same price within walking distance.
Off the hook. Best tacos in the area by far. Handmade tortillas. Mouthwatering al pastor. Cactus tacos are delicious too.

Being someone who has tasted many tacos, from many different places. These were probably the worst tacos I have ever had in my entire life.  The ingredients were fresh, yes. The main part of the tacos however, were just terribly over seasoned. I’m talking about the chicken here. Not only over seasoned, but also over cooked. There was not one incredient, not even cheese, to balance out the horribly salty msg flavor of the chicken.  If you want a good taco, head over to Los Tacos No. 1

The tacos were fresh here! This place is definitely a welcomed sight for DUMBO. Reasonably priced as well and the meet was well seasoned. Not too salty. My only qualm is that the ordering is a little disconnected, where I order but then I hand a ticket to someone to then cook the tacos? I’m sure there are some updates in the works, but if this place gets busy this will be a super long wait. Currently cash only.
